    'books.about.desc': "Because little girls deserve stories that look like them — brave heroines, colorful worlds, messages that stay. These six women changed the world. These six books are here to remember them.",
    'book.ada.name': 'Ada Lovelace', 'book.ada.era': '1815 – 1852 · Mathematics',
    'book.ada.desc': "She wrote the first algorithm in history — a century before the computer was invented. Ada refused to be told what a woman couldn't do.",
    'book.marie.name': 'Marie Curie', 'book.marie.era': '1867 – 1934 · Physics & Chemistry',
    'book.marie.desc': "Two Nobel Prizes. One person. Marie discovered radioactivity in a lab she was denied access to, in an era that closed every door on her. She opened them all.",
    'book.rosa.name': 'Rosa Parks', 'book.rosa.era': '1913 – 2005 · Civil Rights',
    'book.rosa.desc': "On December 1st, 1955, Rosa refused to give up her seat on a bus. That simple act sparked a movement. You don't need to shout to change the world — sometimes you just need to stay seated.",
    'book.amelia.name': 'Amelia Earhart', 'book.amelia.era': '1897 – 1937 · Aviation',
    'book.amelia.desc': "The first woman to fly solo across the Atlantic. Amelia looked at the sky the way others look at the ground — as something that belonged to her.",
    'book.cleo.name': 'Cleopatra', 'book.cleo.era': '69 – 30 BC · Egypt',
    'book.cleo.desc': "Queen of Egypt at 18, polyglot, strategist, philosopher. Cleopatra wasn't just beautiful — she was the most powerful and learned woman of her time.",
    'book.saca.name': 'Sacagawea', 'book.saca.era': '~1788 – 1812 · Exploration',
    'book.saca.desc': "Guide for the Lewis & Clark expedition, she crossed the American wilderness with a newborn on her back. Without her, one of history's greatest explorations would have failed.",
